Reasoning: The paper discusses various interpretations of Dempster-Shafer's model for quantifying degrees of belief, which is relevant to several sub-fields in computer science. The focus on belief updating and dynamic components suggests relevance to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The discussion of probability models and evidentiary value models suggests relevance to information theory (cs.IT) and mathematical analysis (cs.MA). The transferable belief model may also be relevant to social and information networks (cs.SI).
